%% Diagram: Life of a Frame — VSync drives BeginFrame through Viz, the renderer compositor, the main thread, and back to GPU swap and presentation.
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant OS as OS / Display
    participant Viz as Viz (GPU process)
    participant CC as Renderer Compositor (cc)
    participant Main as Renderer Main Thread
    participant GPU as GPU Main Thread

    OS-->>Viz: VSync (~16.67 ms @ 60 Hz)
    Viz->>CC: BeginFrame (per FrameSink)
    CC->>Main: BeginMainFrame (if main-thread damage)
    Main-->>CC: Commit (property trees + display lists)
    Note over CC: Wait for raster, then Activate
    CC-->>Viz: SubmitCompositorFrame (or DidNotProduce)
    Note over Viz: SurfaceAggregator merges frames from every FrameSink
    Viz->>GPU: Draw Frame — record DDLs / GPU commands
    GPU->>GPU: Replay commands on GPU
    GPU->>OS: SwapBuffers / overlay scanout
    OS-->>OS: Display controller scans out at next VBlank
    Note over Viz,OS: If DisplayScheduler hits its deadline, Viz draws what has been submitted. Missing clients fall back to their previous surface.
